Here is an overview of the GoboLinux filesystem tree.  The legacy folders (on
the ":" part of the tree) are links to the corresponding GoboLinux folders.
The legacy folders are excluded from default directory view by [[GoboHide]].

    / 
    |-- Depot                 - user files, ignored by GoboLinux
    |-- Files                 - for resources belonging to the system and to individual programs 
    |   |-- Codecs            - multimedia players use this path to find external codecs.
    |   |-- Compile           - sources and other files used by the Compile tool
    |   |   |-- Archives 
    |   |   |-- Sources 
    |   |   `-- Store 
    |   |-- Descriptions 
    |   |-- Fonts 
    |   |-- Plugins           - for browsers or other applications
    |   `-- Wallpapers 
    |-- Mount                 - mountpoints for filesystems
    |-- Programs              - installed software
    |-- System 
    |   |-- Kernel
    |   |   |-- Boot          - kernel images, config files and programs needed to boot
    |   |   |-- Devices       - device files (managed by Udev).
    |   |   |-- Modules       - loadable kernel modules (device drivers)
    |   |   |-- Objects       - a view of the kernel's device tree 
    |   |   `-- Status        - kernel status files (belonging to the /proc filesystem)
    |   |-- Index             - Links to various resources under /Programs.
    |   |   |-- Environment   - links to program files declaring environment variables. 
    |   |   |-- Executables   - links to files in programs' bin/ and sbin/ directories
    |   |   |-- Headers       - links to files in programs' include/ directories
    |   |   |-- Libraries     - links to files in programs' lib/ directories.
    |   |   |-- Manuals       - documentation resources
    |   |   |    |-- info     - links to files in programs' info directories.
    |   |   |    `-- man{1-9} - links to files in programs' man{1-9} directories.
    |   |   |-- Shared        - links to files in programs' share/ directories.
    |   |   `-- Tasks         - links to programs' boot tasks (from their Resources/Tasks/ directory)
    |   |-- Settings          - system config files and links to files in program's Settings/ directories.
    |   |   `-- BootScripts   - scripts used for boot, symlink to /Programs/BootScripts/Settings/BootScripts/
    |   `-- Variable          - for various log, temporary, transient and spool files
    |       |-- cache 
    |       |-- empty 
    |       |-- lib 
    |       |-- lock 
    |       |-- log 
    |       |-- run 
    |       |-- spool 
    |       `-- tmp
    |-- Users                 - contains users' home directories
    : 
    : 
    :-- etc  -> System/Settings 
    :-- dev  -> System/Kernel/Devices 
    :-- sys  -> System/Kernel/Objects 
    :-- proc -> System/Kernel/Status 
    :-- var  -> System/Variable 
    :-- tmp  -> System/Variable/tmp 
    :-- sbin -> System/Index/bin 
    :-- bin  -> System/Index/bin 
    :-- lib  -> System/Index/lib 
    `-- usr 
        |-- X11R6   -> . 
        |-- local   -> . 
        |-- sbin    -> ../System/Index/bin 
        |-- bin     -> ../System/Index/bin 
        |-- include -> ../System/Index/include 
        |-- lib     -> ../System/Index/lib 
        |-- man     -> ../System/Index/share/man 
        `-- share   -> ../System/Index/share 
